args: 'Course. No way I'd stand by and let\nMyriage Lake get taken!
The imperial army has been conquering\nnearby human villages one by one,\nthen using them as bases to attack ours.
The sylvan villages have been doing their\nbest to fight back, but they have us well\noutnumbered...
Is everyone back in my village okay?
They're hiding in the woods as we speak.
Great. You can leave the rest to us then.\nWe'll send those imperials running in\nno time flat!
If we can liberate the human villages\nthey've taken, that should crush\ntheir momentum.
We can focus our efforts there, while the\nsylvans are buying time.
Acknowledged. Leave it to me.\n▷Hold on, that's not why we're here!◁
This is Laxi. She came to help deliver\nsupplies.
That mission is complete. Now, please\npermit me to fight. I am a COMBAT\nandroid.
If we find ourselves needing help, I'll let\nyou know. But for now...
...Guarding a prisoner is a waste of\nmy abilities.
▷It's an important job.◁\nAnyone can stand watch.\nMy skills are wasted here.
'Scuse me, miss? Can I get some water?\nI'm mighty thirsty.
Request denied. You will wait\nuntil your next mealtime.\n▷Come on, he can have some water!◁
Heh, you're pretty funny, aren't you?\nI've got a kid around your age, you know.
What I wouldn't give to end this fighting\nand get home to her...
▷Oh! You don't want to fight either,\nthen?◁
▷Laxi, please. If he were to die from\ndehydration, it would be your fault.◁
If you are finished, return your cup.\nI will lock the door.
▷Laxi, wait. We should let him go.◁
What?!\n▷He said he doesn't want to fight, right?\nSo why keep him locked up?◁
Incomprehensible! Of course I'm not\nletting him go. I'm locking the door!
Urgh... Mascula! Stop interfering with\nmy operations!
▷I can't keep it up for long, but I CAN\nmake my will known!◁
▷Imperial soldiers are not inherently bad.\nSurely you understand that.◁
I do. But this was a bad idea, Mascula.
He's seen the village now. Which means\nhe's probably gonna...
So that's the size and layout, eh?
We'll storm their base before they even\nknow we're coming! Summon the troops\nfrom the other villages here!
Enemies incoming from the west!\nRight in the watchtower's blind spot...
They must know the village's layout.
▷No... Did he really...?◁\nThe odds are high.
They'll be bringing sufficient numbers to\noverrun this location. You'll need all the\nforces you can get.
I agree. But how do you feel about that,\nMascula?
Mascula, these guys will kill us if we don't\nfight back.
This is my home. And right this moment,\nthose soldiers are hurting people I care\nabout.
Laxi can help us stop them. Please.
▷...Okay. It was my mistake that resulted\nin this situation, so I won't object.◁
Come on, this way! The village is\njust over... Hm?
*sigh* Yeah, yeah, I tricked you. So what?\nThis is war.
Negative. You did not trick me—you\ntricked Mascula.
I was happy to kill you in your cell.

▷Ngh...◁
We are weapons, Mascula. And like
all weapons, we can either be used
to inflict violence or to avert it.
▷I know my inability to fight is strange.◁\nYou're not unable. You simply refuse.\nYou're running away from your duty.
But I am not. I will fight for peace.
That is my duty as an android.
Wait, android? Are you one of those\nweapons that betrayed—
Luca! How are things looking on your end?
Me'n the other sylvans cleaned house,\nno problem!
We were victorious here, too,\nso that just leaves Laxi.
I am fine.\nAll foes have been eliminated.
What the—give a guy a little warning!\nI didn't even hear you coming!
Laxi and Mascula are pretty quiet when\nthey aren't fighting...
Thank you both for your help.

▷(Laxi and Luca are right. Every minute I
spend searching for a peaceful resolution
is another minute the violence of others
goes unchecked.)◁
